Hey facebreak, he's actually right, they are ~184MB per episode, you're talking about ~175MiB.

Nowadays we prefer to use M (mega) as 10^6 as the SI dictates, and Mi (Mebi) as 2^20 IEC dictates.

He probably has a Mac, or works in a HD manufacturing plant, where they use MB instead of MiB (mainly to inflate numbers).

Don't go treating nice fellow pirates as shit please, they are at least better than us leachers. :P
